[SN]TITLE[SN]
Danish health firm to create new jobs in Inverness

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A Danish life science company is to create 30 jobs over the next three years in the Highlands.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
CorporateHealth International ApS is to invest Â£5.7m in establishing a new diagnostics centre at the Inverness Campus.
The centre's staff will analyse images captured by video camera capsules - small devices swallowed by patients.
The capsules offer an alternative to diagnostic endoscopies and colonoscopies.
Highlands and Islands Enterprise is supporting the project with investment of Â£600,000.
CorporateHealth International UK Ltd, a subsidiary of the Danish firm, will run the centre.
